Problem No : 03
Problem Name : Write a c program to check a number is palindrome or not.
Sample Input/Output :  Enter a number : 45954
 is a palindrome number
Process returned 0 (0x0)   execution time : 2.958 s
Press any key to continue.
Coding : 
#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
    int n, c, s=0, r;
    printf("Enter a number : ");
    scanf("%d",&n);
    c=n;
    while (n>0)
    {
        r=n%10;
        s=r+(s*10);
        n=n/10;
    }
    if (c==s)
       printf(" is a palindrome number ");
    else
       printf(" is not a palindrome number ");
    return 0;
}
Result and Discussion : From  the case analysis and the coding  the output and input is same .So , I can say that my code is all right. 


